Looking for a deliciously healthy snack to start off the new year? I got you!

SPICY TANGERINE HUMMUS 

Ingredients
✅️ 15-ounce can chickpeas, reserve liquid from can
✅️ 1 jalapeno
✅️  3/4 @noblerangerines Autumn Honey tangerine, peeled and segmented
✅️  3 cloves garlic
✅️   2 tablespoons tahini
✅️  Juice from one lemon
✅️   1 tablespoon extra-virgin olive oil
✅️  Sea salt and pepper, to taste

Instructions
1️⃣ Add chickpeas, tangerine, garlic,  jalapeno, tahini, and lemon juice and to the container of a food processor.
2️⃣ Slowly add the olive oil while pureeing.
Slowly add just enough reserved liquid from the chickpeas, to create a smooth, creamy texture if needed. I used one tablespoon.
Season with salt and pepper as desired.

Serve with fresh veggies and crackers for dipping.

Would also be amazing on pizza and sandwiches!

IT'S CHERRY SEASON! One of my favorite times of the year 🍒
Celebrate with me by making this Cherry Smash Old Fashioned 😍

Ingredients
▢ 4 Cherries 
▢ 2 ½ oz Bourbon - Whiskey will work too
▢ 1 wedge Lemon
▢ 1 tsp Maple syrup - simple syrup is an easy substitute

Instructions
🍒 Remove the pits from 4 moon cherries, then cut the cherries in half.
🍒 Place the cherries on the bottom of your favorite glass, squeeze in the juice from one lemon wedge, and add in the maple syrup.
🍒 Give the cherries a good smashing. I used a big spoon. You want to release all of that incredible cherry juice.
🍒 Add in the bourbon.
🍒 Stir well.
🍒 Add ice.
🍒 Top with a slice of lemon and a cherry.

CHEERS!

For the 1st time EVER (in over 20 years!) we enjoyed the ride. This summer was a little different for my family...

We always drive to Michigan...
30 hrs. To spend time with family ❤️ But this year my daughter and I did the drive solo. In an RV!

My son was at college and my husband flew with him to MI for a long weekend.

So, my daughter and I decided to enjoy the ride. We stopped and saw some sites...We slept in hotels beds. Ate food other than gas station food and made memories!

Stop #1 - Chattanooga. Still took us 10 hrs to get there, but it was our first time there and it was awesome! We ate at a great taco place and brought moon pies. I also got the RV stuck...but we won't talk about that. Then we checked out Ruby Falls! We have seen the sign COUNTLESS times on I-75, and it was cool to see it.

Stop #2 - Columbus Ohio. 8 hr drive. We stayed right by Easton Mall....coolest mall I've been to and I've been to a LOT. And we shopped our hearts out. And ate. And had great coffee! 

Stop #3 - FAMILY FUN! More on that soon. 

My message to you...slow down and enjoy the ride. I have been driving up to Michigan every year for 22 years. Sometimes we don't Stop at all. Sometimes we stop once. Never, ever, ever have we stopped and looked at anything along the way. It was amazing to do that with my daughter ❤️

Have more adventures!

Make more memories!

Stop along the way!
